1.5 Monolith vs Microservices: Architecture Delta
In monolith mode all of the above run in one binary. The only things that change in microservices
mode are:
Each component runs as a separate Deployment (or StatefulSet for ingesters)
A memberlist service enables ring gossip between pods
Object store becomes mandatory (no local disk)
Each component’s target flag changes ( -target=distributor , etc.)
NetworkPolicy must open inter-component gRPC traffic
2. How-To
2.1 Pre-Migration Checklist
[ ] Object store provisioned (MinIO on-cluster, or AWS S3 / Ceph RGW)
[ ] StorageClass available for Ingester PVCs (ReadWriteOnce, fast SSD-backed)
[ ] OpenShift project/namespace created with resource quotas defined
[ ] SCC (SecurityContextConstraints) reviewed — Pyroscope needs UID flexibility
[ ] ServiceAccount created with object store IAM role or Secret
[ ] Existing monolith data migrated or retention window accepted as loss
[ ] Grafana datasource URL to be updated post-cutover
[ ] Java agent ENV vars updated in all app Deployments (server address)
[ ] DNS/service naming conventions agreed (internal vs external routes)
2.2 Namespace and RBAC Setup
# namespace
apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
name: observability-pyroscope
labels:
openshift.io/cluster-monitoring: "false"
---
# ServiceAccount
apiVersion: v1
kind: ServiceAccount
metadata:
name: pyroscope
namespace: observability-pyroscope
---
# ClusterRole for self-discovery (memberlist requires pod listing)
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: Role
metadata:
name: pyroscope-memberlist
namespace: observability-pyroscope
rules:
- apiGroups: [""]
resources: ["pods"]
verbs: ["get", "list", "watch"]
---
apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1
kind: RoleBinding
metadata:
name: pyroscope-memberlist
namespace: observability-pyroscope
subjects:
- kind: ServiceAccount
name: pyroscope
roleRef:
kind: Role
name: pyroscope-memberlist
apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io
2.3 SecurityContextConstraints (OpenShift SCC)
Pyroscope containers run as non-root but need a consistent UID for WAL file ownership. Use a
custom SCC or the built-in restricted-v2 if UID ranges allow.
apiVersion: security.openshift.io/v1
kind: SecurityContextConstraints
metadata:
name: pyroscope-scc
allowPrivilegedContainer: false
allowPrivilegeEscalation: false
runAsUser:
type: MustRunAsRange
uidRangeMin: 10001
uidRangeMax: 10001
seLinuxContext:
type: MustRunAs
fsGroup:
type: MustRunAs
ranges:
- min: 10001
max: 10001
volumes:
- configMap
- secret
- persistentVolumeClaim
- emptyDir
users:
- system:serviceaccount:observability-pyroscope:pyroscope
2.4 Object Store Secret
apiVersion: v1
kind: Secret
metadata:
name: pyroscope-objstore
namespace: observability-pyroscope
type: Opaque
stringData:
objstore.yaml: |
type: S3
config:
bucket: pyroscope-blocks
endpoint: minio.minio.svc.cluster.local:9000
access_key: <ACCESS_KEY>
secret_key: <SECRET_KEY>
insecure: true # set false for TLS
signature_version2: false
2.5 Memberlist Service (Gossip Ring)
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
name: pyroscope-memberlist
namespace: observability-pyroscope
spec:
type: ClusterIP
clusterIP: None publishNotReadyAddresses: true
selector:
app.kubernetes.io/name: pyroscope
ports:
- name: memberlist
port: 7946
protocol: TCP
- name: memberlist-udp
port: 7946
protocol: UDP
# headless — required for memberlist DNS
2.6 Core ConfigMap (Shared Across All Components)
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
name: pyroscope-config
namespace: observability-pyroscope
data:
config.yaml: |
memberlist:
join_members:
- pyroscope-memberlist.observability-pyroscope.svc.cluster.local:7946
pyroscopedb:
data_path: /data/pyroscope
min_block_duration: 2h
max_block_duration: 24h
storage:
backend: s3
s3:
bucket_name: pyroscope-blocks
endpoint: minio.minio.svc.cluster.local:9000
access_key_id: ${AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID}
secret_access_key: ${AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY}
insecure: true
limits:
max_query_lookback: 30d
max_query_parallelism: 16
ingestion_rate_mb: 4
ingestion_burst_size_mb: 8
compactor:
sharding_enabled: true
store_gateway:
sharding_enabled: true
2.7 Deploying Each Component
Distributor (Deployment — stateless):
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
name: pyroscope-distributor
namespace: observability-pyroscope
spec:
replicas: 2
selector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/component: distributor
template:
metadata:
labels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: pyroscope
app.kubernetes.io/component: distributor
spec:
serviceAccountName: pyroscope
securityContext:
runAsUser: 10001
fsGroup: 10001
containers:
- name: pyroscope
image: grafana/pyroscope:1.7.0
args:
- -target=distributor
- -config.file=/etc/pyroscope/config.yaml
ports:
- name: http
containerPort: 4040
- name: grpc
containerPort: 9095
- name: memberlist
containerPort: 7946
resources:
requests:
cpu: 500m
memory: 512Mi
limits:
cpu: 2
memory: 1Gi
volumeMounts:
- name: config
mountPath: /etc/pyroscope
volumes:
- name: config
configMap:
name: pyroscope-config
---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
name: pyroscope-distributor
namespace: observability-pyroscope
spec:
selector:
app.kubernetes.io/component: distributor
ports:
- name: http
port: 4040
targetPort: 4040
- name: grpc
port: 9095
targetPort: 9095
Ingester (StatefulSet — stateful WAL):
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
name: pyroscope-ingester
namespace: observability-pyroscope
spec:
replicas: 3
serviceName: pyroscope-ingester-headless
selector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/component: ingester
template:
metadata:
labels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: pyroscope
app.kubernetes.io/component: ingester
spec:
serviceAccountName: pyroscope
securityContext:
runAsUser: 10001
fsGroup: 10001
containers:
- name: pyroscope
image: grafana/pyroscope:1.7.0
args:
- -target=ingester
- -config.file=/etc/pyroscope/config.yaml
ports:
- name: http
containerPort: 4040
- name: grpc
containerPort: 9095
- name: memberlist
containerPort: 7946
resources:
requests:
cpu: 1
memory: 2Gi
limits:
cpu: 4
memory: 8Gi
volumeMounts:
- name: config
mountPath: /etc/pyroscope
- name: data
mountPath: /data/pyroscope
volumes:
- name: config
configMap:
name: pyroscope-config
volumeClaimTemplates:
- metadata:
name: data
spec:
accessModes: [ReadWriteOnce]
storageClassName: fast-ssd
resources:
requests:
storage: 50Gi
2.8 NetworkPolicy
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
name: pyroscope-internal
namespace: observability-pyroscope
spec:
podSelector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: pyroscope
policyTypes:
- Ingress
- Egress
ingress:
# Allow all Pyroscope pods to talk to each other (gRPC + memberlist)
- from:
- podSelector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: pyroscope
ports:
- port: 9095 # gRPC
- port: 7946 # memberlist TCP
- port: 4040 # HTTP
# Allow app pods (Java agent) to push to distributor
- from:
- namespaceSelector:
matchLabels:
app-tier: backend
ports:
- port: 4040
# Allow Grafana to query frontend
- from:
- namespaceSelector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: grafana
ports:
- port: 4040
egress:
# Object store (MinIO / S3)
- to:
- namespaceSelector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: minio
ports:
- port: 9000
# DNS
- ports:
- port: 53
protocol: UDP
- port: 53
protocol: TCP
# Memberlist UDP
- to:
- podSelector:
matchLabels:
app.kubernetes.io/name: pyroscope
ports:
- port: 7946
protocol: UDP
2.9 Updating Java Agents in App Deployments
Change only the PYROSCOPE_SERVER_ADDRESS — everything else stays the same:
# Before (monolith VM)
env:
- name: PYROSCOPE_SERVER_ADDRESS
value: "http://pyroscope-vm.internal:4040"
# After (microservices on OpenShift)
env:
- name: PYROSCOPE_SERVER_ADDRESS
value: "http://pyroscope-distributor.observability-pyroscope.svc.cluster.local:4040"
- name: PYROSCOPE_APPLICATION_NAME
value: "my-vertx-service.$(MY_POD_NAMESPACE)" # namespace-scoped naming
- name: PYROSCOPE_PROFILER_EVENT
value: "wall"
- name: PYROSCOPE_UPLOAD_INTERVAL
value: "15s"
2.10 Cutover Sequence
Day 0: Deploy all Pyroscope components (canary namespace, no agent traffic)
Day 1: Point 10% of app pods at new distributor (feature flag / env var)
Day 2: Validate profiles appear in Grafana; check ingester WAL health
Day 3: Point 50% of pods at new distributor
Day 4: Full cutover — update all Deployments/DeploymentConfigs
Day 5: Decommission VM monolith (keep 1 week for rollback window)
