OrgID )
4. Tutorial
4.1 Deploying to a Dev Namespace (End-to-End Lab)
Goal: Get one ingested profile visible in Grafana Explore in under 30 minutes.
Step 1 — Create namespace and apply configs:
oc new-project observability-pyroscope
oc apply -f pyroscope-scc.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-serviceaccount.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-objstore-secret.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-config.yaml
Step 2 — Deploy components (in order):
# Memberlist service first
oc apply -f pyroscope-memberlist-svc.yaml
# Then components (order matters for ring bootstrap)
oc apply -f pyroscope-ingester-statefulset.yaml
oc wait --for=condition=Ready pod -l app.kubernetes.io/component=ingester --timeout=120s
oc apply -f pyroscope-distributor-deployment.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-query-frontend-deployment.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-querier-deployment.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-store-gateway-deployment.yaml
oc apply -f pyroscope-compactor-deployment.yaml
Step 3 — Verify ring health:
# Port-forward the distributor
oc port-forward svc/pyroscope-distributor 4040:4040
# Check ring status
curl http://localhost:4040/ring
# Expect: all ingesters ACTIVE, healthy: true
Step 4 — Send a test profile:
# Generate a fake pprof payload and push
curl -X POST http://localhost:4040/ingest \
-F "name=test-app.cpu{}" \
-F "format=pprof" \
-F "sampleRate=100" \
--data-binary @/tmp/test.pprof
Step 5 — Add Grafana datasource:
URL: http://pyroscope-query-frontend.observability-pyroscope.svc.cluster.local:4040
Type: Grafana Pyroscope
Step 6 — Validate in Explore:
Open Grafana → Explore → Pyroscope datasource → select see a flame graph.
test-app.cpu → Run query. You should
5. Capacity Planning
5.1 Capacity Model Inputs
Gather these from your current monolith VM before sizing:
Input How to Measure Example
Active series Unique {app, labels} combos 200
Profiles/sec (ingest
rate)
pyroscope_distributor_received_profiles_total
rate 400/s
Avg profile size pyroscope_distributor_received_bytes_total / count 8 KB
Upload interval (agent) PYROSCOPE_UPLOAD_INTERVAL 15s
Retention Business requirement 30 days
Query concurrency Peak concurrent Grafana users 10
App instances Pods running the Java agent 50
5.2 Ingestion Bandwidth Formula
Ingest bandwidth (MB/s) = (App instances × avg_profile_size_KB) / upload_interval_seconds / 1024
Example:
= (50 pods × 8 KB) / 15s / 1024
= 400 KB/s
= 0.39 MB/s
Per distributor pod limit: 4 MB/s (default `ingestion_rate_mb`)
→ 1 distributor pod covers this load with headroom
→ Run 2 for HA
5.3 Object Store Sizing Formula
Daily storage = ingest_bandwidth_MB/s × 86400s × compression_ratio
Pyroscope compression ratio ≈ 0.15 (parquet + zstd is very efficient)
Example:
= 0.39 MB/s × 86400 × 0.15
= ~5 GB/day
30-day retention:
= 5 GB × 30 = 150 GB object store
Add 20% headroom for compactor temp space:
= 180 GB total object store
5.4 Ingester Memory Formula
Ingester memory = (active_series × avg_series_size_bytes × replication_factor)
+ WAL overhead (typically 2× active data)
Avg series size in Pyroscope ≈ 100 KB (profile samples + index)
Example (200 series, RF=3, 3 ingesters):
Active data per ingester = (200 × 100 KB × 3) / 3 ingesters = 20 MB
WAL overhead = 2× = 40 MB
→ Very low for 200 series; minimum 2 Gi request is safe
For 5,000 series:
= (5000 × 100 KB × 3) / 3 = 500 MB active
WAL = 1 GB
→ Request 2 Gi, limit 8 Gi
